The Elders’ Caucus of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Osun State, pioneered by the first interim chairman of the party and former governor, Chief Bisi Akande has said the reelection of Governor Adegboyega Oyetola has been ordained by God. The caucus in a communiqué signed by its chairman and ex-Secretary to the State Government, Chief Sola Akinwumi after a stakeholder meeting held in Ilobu, Irepodun Local Government area on Thursday disclosed that they have resolved to throw weight behind Oyetola.   Prioritising people     Was it a warning shot?     Dissociative identity disorder   “God backed Oyetola in the first term and we are certain that his reelection during 2022 governorship election slated for July 16th has been ordained. Victory is sure for our party. “We appreciate all steps and activities undertaking by the Governor towards ensuring quick transformation of our State through his numerous developmental projects spread across the State. “We enjoined residents to continue to give their support towards re-election of Oyetola on July 16. Let us troop out to vote for re-election of Governor Gboyega Oyetola.”